Third pereiopod
(
Fig. 8c, d
): dactylus 2.3 (3 × according to 
De Man 1897
) × as long as breadth and bearing 7 spines (including terminal spine). Propodus 4.8 (4 × according to 
De Man 1897
) × dactylus and 7.25 (9 × according to 
De Man, 1897
) × long as broad with numerous minute spines arranged along inner margin. Carpus 0.66 × long as propodus, with large spine at anterior end and 2 minute spines on inner margin. Merus broad, 1.94 × carpus length. Merus with 1small and 3 large spines on posterior margin.

First pleopod of male (
Fig. 8g , h
): endopod broad and large, 0.93 × exopod length. Appendix interna present.

Second male pleopod (
Fig. 8i , j
): appendix masculina remarkably long, 4.82 × appendix interna and 1.1 × endopod. Several small spines present on entire surface of anterior half.

Uropod (
Fig. 8m
): 15 diaeresis spinules.
